description:
SUMMARY:

After having his life saved by Matt Murdock, Leander natchios is more than willing to tell him all he knows about the assassin Bullseye. So he and Elektra go to Poindexters ( Bullseyes ) hideout. There they find evidence of his next hit, a lawyer who made a copy of the ledger the Kingpin was trying to get ahold of. They go to City hall to stop the killing. There the two of them fight Bullseye to a stand still, but he still ends up killing the lawyer they tried to save, and got away with the briefcase he was carrying. They search the dead body to discover that he taped the ledger to his chest. seeing this Elektra knocks Matt out and takes the ledger.
name: Devil's Due: Part 4

description: The battle lines have been drawn, but will Elektra find herself on the same side of the law as Matt Murdock? The two ex-lovers come face-to-face with Wilson Fisk and his mysterious assassin, with the fate of more than just Elektra's family hanging in the balance. Don't miss the stunning conclusion!
name: Devil's Due: Part 5
A pain in the ass for Sayoko
Cheryl in the Morning; Getting Along Swimmingly!; Looking For Mr. Mumps!

description: Watch out, bikini lovers, here comes Cheryl in a summer-ific issue! Featuring flashy fashions from our radical readers! In "Creature Feature on Party Beach," Rick Goreman, a low-budget horror movie maker, stumbles upon Cheryl's beach party and comes up with a money-saving idea: set up hidden cameras and film the kids as they find his 'haunted' pirate ship! Plus: It's a 'fun day on the runway' when Cheryl enlists the gang to model in her rainforest benefit fashion show "Jungle Blossom!" And Cheryl gives her eyeballs a workout ? by watching the body builders on the beach in "Beauty And The Beach!"
name: Creature Feature On Beach Party

description: "Take The Mummy And Run": Move over, Cleopatra, Cheryl intends to be the queen of the gala opening of the museum's new Egyptian wing, sponsored by her parents, of course! And she wouldn't mind being the queen of "Dr. Carter", the "renowned archeologist" who's a consultant to the collection. The good doctor may not be all he seems, however, and it may be too late before the Blossom's realize egypt 'em! Also: When the boys get on their boards, they're bored with bikinis, until "Skateboard Blossom" dons one and gets on a skateboard of her own! Plus: Cheryl answers the age-old question: am I my brother's fashion's consultan, in "Fashion Emergency!"
name: Take The Mummy And Run; FAshion Emergency

description: "It's A Maze Thing": At an outdoor charity function, Cheryl wanders into a garden maze. Imagine her surprise when she bumps into her rival, Veronica! Worse yet, they're both lost! A strange alliance "blooms" as these two team up to find their way out. Can they "weed" out their differences and "sow the seeds" of friendship? It's one "a-MAZE-ing" tale that will really "grow" on you! Plus: It's tricks, not treats, when Cheryl and Jason wear the same costumes as Archie and Veronica at Betty's Halloween party in "Identity Crisis!" Will Archie mistake one vampy rich girl for another? Will Betty be swept away by an Archie impostor?
name: It's A Maze Thing

description: "Holi-Daze": Tis the season to try to outdo each other with elaborate holiday parties, at least for Cheryl and Veronica! Will they deck the halls,  or each other?! Looks like a job for everyone's favorite angel, Betty!
name: Holi-Daze

description: "To Catch A Falling Star": Cheryl is livin' la vida loca, literally, when she tries to snag an interview with elusive pop star Martin Ricky for her fashion magazine! She'll have to get through his bodyguard first, however. What is Martin's secret, anyway, and why is he keeping it from the public? If we know Cheryl, she'll get all the answers, and then some!
name: To Catch A Falling Star

description: "C'est La Ski": After a full year of touring, hot, all-girl singing group B*Magic is looking forward to fun and relaxation at the ski lodge, but Cheryl has something else in mind, namely a photo spread of the group's vacation. Using her every ounce of journalistic integrity, not!  Cheryl attaches a micro-camera to her puppy Sugar's dog collar! Will Cheryl get the pictures she wants, or just another lesson in consideration?
name: C'est La Ski

description: "In Your Dreams": When Cheryl finds herself constantly dreaming about Jughead, she quits eating cold pizza before bedtime. When the dreams continue, however, she's really in a dilemma. Could she actually be in love with Jughead? Impossible! At her wit's end, she enlists the help of Dilton to try and stop these "nightmares" about Jughead. She learns that the only way to stop these dreams is to kiss Jughead and find out the real deal.
"Bug Off!": Things get "hairy" when Cheryl gets into the "bug clip" craze! "Gopher Broke": Cheryl has her own "war of the roses", or should we say "rodents," when a gopher devours her garden!
name: Bug Off!

description: Guest-starring Sabrina! "Midsummer's Magic": It's, rich meets witch' when Sabrina guest stars, both as a teenager and (via flashback) as the pre-teen currently enjoying success in her hot ABC/UPN animated series! A chance sighting of Sabrina on the beach leaves Jason love struck, but Cheryl feels other emotions as she flashes back in time to when she and Sabrina were in summer camp! Cheryl didn't endear herself to her fellow campers, but Sabrina had compassion for her, being, different' herself. Until Cheryl started hitting on Harvey, that is! Sabrina whipped up a little something to, scare' Cheryl home, and ever since, Cheryl hasn't forgotten that terrifying episode! Will Cheryl be able to face her, haunted' past?
name: Midsummer's Magic

description: "Phantom of the Fun House": A stroll on the beach with Archie and the gang leads to an amazing discovery, a defunct boardwalk amusement park! Curious, the teens check it out. Have they stumbled upon a haunted ghost park? The answer will thrill and chill you!
name: Phantom Of The Funhouse

description: "The Big Break-up," Part One: Could it be true? Has Betty actually dumped Archie for good? And just who is the chivalrous, romantic, conscientious new man in her life named Adam? And why is Archie noticing Betty more than ever... now that she's gone?! Have Archie's fickle ways finally caught up to him? It's a story no Archie Comics fan can afford to miss!
name: The Big Break-Up, Part One

description: The last 16 of the exclusive WildGuard Internet comic strips are presented in the conclusion of this miniseries. Also this issue, Snapback recalls the day he told two of his fellow Tri-County Power Patrol members he was auditioning for WildGuard. The 'Where Are They Now?' feature spotlights rejected contenders, Strong-Bot and Running Girl.
name: Audition Tapes; Messages; Expectations

description: NOTE: This issue reprints Marvel Two-In-One Vol.1 #50.
name: Remeberance Of Things Past
